description:
There is a problem with SPARQL (Virtuoso version 07.20.3229) that occurs e.g. on the sparql endpoint : https://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/sparql
with the query below. The problem occurs with these conditions:  two subqueries, a group by and a filter exists  in the second subquery . In this case, the join between the two subqueries fails and there are false results. If the filter exists BGP is replaced by BGP (that is the same BGP without filter exists) the join works all right.
prefix hsc: <http://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/schema/>
prefix dc: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
prefix org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

select distinct ?n
where {
{select ?n where {
?doc dc:creator ?s .
?doc dc:issued ?date .
filter (year(?date) >= 2019)
?s hsc:structure/org:unitOf <https://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/structure/13009> .
?s hsc:person/foaf:name ?n
} }

{select ?n where {
?doc dc:creator ?s .
?doc dc:issued ?date .
filter (year(?date) >= 2019)
?s hsc:structure/org:unitOf <https://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/structure/13009> .
?s hsc:person/foaf:name ?n .

filter exists { ?doc dc:creator/hsc:person/foaf:name ?m  filter regex(?m, "Olivier") }
} group by ?n
}
}

The query below, where filter exists { BGP } is replaced by BGP, return correct results:
prefix hsc: <http://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/schema/>
prefix dc: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
prefix org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

select distinct ?n
where {
{select ?n where {
?doc dc:creator ?s .
?doc dc:issued ?date .
filter (year(?date) >= 2019)
?s hsc:structure/org:unitOf <https://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/structure/13009> .
?s hsc:person/foaf:name ?n
} }

{select ?n where {
?doc dc:creator ?s .
?doc dc:issued ?date .
filter (year(?date) >= 2019)
?s hsc:structure/org:unitOf <https://data.archives-ouvertes.fr/structure/13009> .
?s hsc:person/foaf:name ?n .

?doc dc:creator/hsc:person/foaf:name ?m  filter regex(?m, "Olivier")
} group by ?n
}
}
